This course will cover specific language aspects such as developing basicfunctions of English language skills such as reading, listening, writing, speaking,vocabulary and grammar.
Course Learning Outcome ( CLO): At the end of the course the student will be able to do:
Speak with accuracy, fluency, and confidence using appropriate expressions indifferent contexts.
Explain and infer various reading and listening materials.
Apply variety of grammatical skills in various communicative contexts
Make use of contextual clues to acquire meanings of unfamiliar words from context.
